The user updates his self-description as follows: I favor single‑artist "very best" collections that showcase an expressive lead vocalist — warm, intimate vocal presence, melodic storytelling, tasteful acoustic and country‑rock arrangements, and career‑spanning sequencing that highlights variety within one singer. I like CDs where songcraft and vocal nuance are front and center: clear, natural mastering that preserves dynamics, concise tracks and thoughtful sequencing that reveal an artist’s range from ballads to rootsy uptempo numbers. From my past tastes I retain a preference for clear mastering, concise track lengths, brisk mood changes when they serve clarity, and well‑curated compilations (including lively retro/rockabilly multi‑artist sets) that keep each track distinct. I dislike over‑produced, homogenized pop/dance mixes with relentless compression and club‑only backbeats that bury vocal detail; long, drawn‑out jams that sag; and albums whose production flattens contrast so tracks blend into a single, tiring timbre.

The positive CD has the following updated information: The Very Best of Linda Ronstadt — Folk/Contemporary Folk: Career-spanning single-artist collection spotlighting warm, intimate lead vocals, melodic storytelling and tasteful acoustic/country-rock arrangements. Clear, natural mastering preserves dynamics; concise sequencing highlights contrast from tender ballads to rootsy uptempo numbers for vocal-centric listeners.

